metadata.description:
After a strange accident sidelines Eureka's sheriff, U.S. Marshal Jack Carter takes over the investigation into the mysterious phenomenon that led to the death of a resident. 
Carter learns about the secret purpose of the town while trying to re-establish a connection with his angry and bitter daughter, Zoe. He develops a friendly working relationship with government liaison Allison Blake and meets some of the more eccentric residents of Eureka.
metadata.title: Pilot
metadata.name: Eureka - Pilot

metadata.description: Carter and the other citizens of Eureka attend the funeral of Susan Perkins. Much to their surprise, Ms. Perkins makes a return to Eureka as a woman who is very much alive!
metadata.title: Many Happy Returns
metadata.name: Eureka - Many Happy Returns

metadata.description: Jack Carter accidentally shoots Henry while suffering from short-term memory loss, meanwhile a visit from a noted scientist may hold clues into to his sudden memory loss.
metadata.title: Before I Forget
metadata.name: Eureka - Before I Forget

metadata.description: Spencer is apparently abducted by aliens and then returned to earth the next day inside a crop circle. Also, the town is visited by the congressman whose committee is responsible for its government funding.
metadata.title: Alienated
metadata.name: Eureka - Alienated

metadata.description: After a lab accident, Global Dynamics researcher Carl Carlson is expelled from Eureka due to lack of results. Later, it is discovered that the accident has unlocked hidden abilities in Carl. Meanwhile, Jack does his best to avoid a physical.
metadata.title: Invincible
metadata.name: Eureka - Invincible

metadata.description: After Fargo and Spencer accidentally activate a doomsday device, Carter must help Dr. Irwin Thatcher, an aging scientist, to shut down the device.
metadata.title: Dr. Nobel
metadata.name: Eureka - Dr. Nobel

metadata.description: Carter investigates an unusual car accident. Meanwhile, Stark is under stress to produce results on a project.
metadata.title: Blink
metadata.name: Eureka - Blink

metadata.description: When the return of Eureka's star pupil causes problems all over town, Stark is forced to make a hard choice. Carter attempts to track down Zoe who has run off with the former resident.
metadata.title: Right as Raynes
metadata.name: Eureka - Right as Raynes

metadata.description: Fargo invents a device that bridges the gap between computers and human brains
metadata.title: Primal
metadata.name: Eureka - Primal

metadata.description: Strange behavior is affecting the whole town except Sheriff Carter and Zoe. The father and daughter team must find the cause while Stark makes a decision that could affect the world.
metadata.title: Purple Haze
metadata.name: Eureka - Purple Haze

metadata.description: S.A.R.A.H - the artificial intelligence that runs Carter's house takes him and a group of residents hostage in an intervention to keep Carter in Eureka. Meanwhile her root program B.R.A.D activates and turns the situation deadly.
metadata.title: H.O.U.S.E. Rules
metadata.name: Eureka - H.O.U.S.E. Rules

metadata.description: Stark is given a chance to try the top-secret Artifact. Once it's tested, Eureka warps into the future and ends up in 2010, where the town is different.
metadata.title: Once in a Lifetime
metadata.name: Eureka - Once in a Lifetime

metadata.description: A man bursts into flames. Elsewhere, Carter and Deacon are reaccustoming to the timeline restored in "Once in a Lifetime."
metadata.title: Phoenix Rising
metadata.name: Eureka - Phoenix Rising

metadata.description: Carter requests Stark's help after Fargo accidentally activates a personal force field, which causes mayhem.
metadata.title: Try, Try Again
metadata.name: Eureka - Try, Try Again

metadata.description: An isolated deep freeze trigger causes a chain reaction of sudden weather changes in Eureka.
metadata.title: Unpredictable
metadata.name: Eureka - Unpredictable

metadata.description: After receiving a hit to the head, Carter finds that he is in a parallel Eureka. He discovers that the residents of the parallel Eureka are disappearing.
metadata.title: Games People Play
metadata.name: Eureka - Games People Play

metadata.description: Space debris threatens Eureka's existence after it accumulates into a large cloud. Carter investigates in an effort to avert potential disaster.
metadata.title: Duck, Duck Goose
metadata.name: Eureka - Duck, Duck Goose

metadata.description: A toxic spill seems to cause Eureka's residents to share their dreams. Initially the situation is amusing, but turns dire after the dream sharing is discovered to have a lethal attribute. The situation becomes more complicated, when Carter finds out that the spill is not the cause.
metadata.title: Noche de Sueños
metadata.name: Eureka - Noche de Sueños

metadata.description: A man who turns out to be Fargo's grandfather has been cryogenically frozen for 50 years. He is awakened from his slumber by accident with no recollection of how he was frozen. In addition to that, it seems that he is the father of lots of technologies at Eureka.
metadata.title: Family Reunion
metadata.name: Eureka - Family Reunion

metadata.description: An experiment about the big bang theory seems to be the cause for Eureka's finest to become dumber and dumber, including everyone involved in the experiment. When it comes to the verge of destroying Global Dynamics, the fate of the town lies in the hands of Jack Carter and the team of scientists he assembles, amongst them the newest member of the town, an anti-social genius.
metadata.title: E=MC...?
metadata.name: Eureka - E=MC...?

metadata.description: Strange happenings and spreading radiation at Global Dynamics lead to speculations that an abandoned research project concerning invisibility might have been revived. When Sheriff Carter accidentally becomes involved, the effects of invisibility threaten his life.
metadata.title: Sight Unseen
metadata.name: Eureka - Sight Unseen

files.name: Eureka - God is in the Details

metadata.description: Zoe and her friends lose their voices, but whatever is causing the symptoms has an even worse effect on Allison and her only hope comes from an unusual source.
metadata.title: God is in the Details
metadata.name: Eureka - God is in the Details

metadata.description: Eureka's air-conditioning system develops a fault, causing sexually tense situations, when the female residents suddenly become attracted to Carter due to bacteria.
metadata.title: Maneater
metadata.name: Eureka - Maneater

metadata.description: The town along with its residents mysteriously start to deconstruct. The prime suspect is an artist who couldn't get along with Stark when he was working at Global Dynamics.
metadata.title: All That Glitters
metadata.name: Eureka - All That Glitters

files.name: Eureka - A Night at Global Dynamics

metadata.description: Carter and Stark must work together as an aggressive virus is sweeping across Eureka, while Kevin's life is in danger.
metadata.title: A Night at Global Dynamics
metadata.name: Eureka - A Night at Global Dynamics

metadata.description: Eureka is threatened by an intelligent drone with "issues" after an anti-missile test. Meanwhile, Eva Thorne, nicknamed "The Fixer" after dismantling and rebuilding several corporations, arrives in Eureka to evaluate Global Dynamics' expenditures.
metadata.title: Bad to the Drone
metadata.name: Eureka - Bad to the Drone

metadata.description: Sheriff Carter and Allison investigate the disappearance of a scientist from a sealed biosphere. Meanwhile, "The Fixer" attempts to make Eureka's ventures more profitable.
metadata.title: What About Bob?
metadata.name: Eureka - What About Bob?

metadata.description: The town's annual dog show gets into full swing complete with exploding robotic canines. Meanwhile, Sheriff Carter experiences an isolated earthquake, Zoe contemplates quitting the accelerated physics program, and Allison starts fitting her wedding dress.
metadata.title: Best in Faux
metadata.name: Eureka - Best in Faux

metadata.description: On Allison and Stark's wedding day, Sheriff Carter finds himself stuck in a time loop, causing him to experience the same lousy day over and over again. Meanwhile, Sheriff Carter's sister, Lexi visits Eureka.
metadata.title: I Do Over
metadata.name: Eureka - I Do Over

metadata.description: When an Egyptian tomb is opened at Global Dynamics, strange things start to happen, leading Fargo to believe it is the mummy's curse. The mummy, however, has disappeared, and Carter investigates.
metadata.title: Show Me the Mummy
metadata.name: Eureka - Show Me the Mummy

metadata.description: A mysterious "superhero" who can walk through walls is causing a ruckus in Eureka. Meanwhile, Zoe and her friends become stranded with Zane Donovan in an abandoned subterranean facility.
metadata.title: Phased and Confused
metadata.name: Eureka - Phased and Confused

metadata.description: The town's mayoral race is disrupted when Zoe's science partner inadvertently causes a second sun to appear over Eureka.
metadata.title: Here Come the Suns
metadata.name: Eureka - Here Come the Suns

metadata.description: When a potentially world-altering scientific discovery from Eureka's past finally comes to light, can anyone be trusted with it? The question is far from rhetorical for Carter: Zoe's life is in immediate danger and Eva Thorne knows why.
metadata.title: From Fear to Eternity
metadata.name: Eureka - From Fear to Eternity

metadata.description: A new sheriff arrives in Eureka that turns out to be a robot that can change into human form (with mixed results). The town really needs the new sheriff as the town's gravity seems to be acting up.
metadata.title: Welcome Back, Carter
metadata.name: Eureka - Welcome Back, Carter

metadata.description: Deputy Lupo stands in as the acting sheriff while Carter undergoes his annual physical, but she's not acting like herself.
metadata.title: Your Face or Mine?
metadata.name: Eureka - Your Face or Mine?

metadata.description: Tess Fontana (Jaime Ray Newman) shakes things up in Carter’s world when she’s brought in by Allison to re-open Section Five.
metadata.title: Insane in the P-Brane
metadata.name: Eureka - Insane in the P-Brane

files.name: Eureka - It's Not Easy Being Green

metadata.description: A bowling tournament brings a rival science team from Area 51 to town, leaving Carter investigating practical jokes that escalate in scope and destruction as the competition progresses.
metadata.title: It's Not Easy Being Green
metadata.name: Eureka - It's Not Easy Being Green

metadata.description: Teenagers construct an odd building in a Eureka field while asleep.
metadata.title: If You Build It...
metadata.name: Eureka - If You Build It...

metadata.description: Henry's 20-year-old project returns with more on board than it left with.
metadata.title: Ship Happens
metadata.name: Eureka - Ship Happens

metadata.description: Jack investigates the deaths of scientists who drowned in less than liquid circumstances. Meanwhile, Allison's baby shower goes green.
metadata.title: Shower the People
metadata.name: Eureka - Shower the People

metadata.description: It's a busy day for Global Dynamics and Eureka as Allison's labor begins during a sonic cleaning of the company, and the townspeople exhibit Alzheimer's disease at the same time.
metadata.title: You Don't Know Jack
metadata.name: Eureka - You Don't Know Jack

metadata.description: Tess hopes her first day in charge of Global will be uneventful; the arrival of an Arctic ice core brings a new Ice Age to Eureka
metadata.title: Have an Ice Day
metadata.name: Eureka - Have an Ice Day

files.name: Eureka - What Goes Around Comes Around

metadata.description: Zoe prepares to leave for college. Tess receives a job offer in Australia. A magnetic disturbance hovers above Eureka.
metadata.title: What Goes Around Comes Around
metadata.name: Eureka - What Goes Around Comes Around

metadata.description: Dr. Grant, a former resident of the town, causes serious alarm with his unexpected return. His romantic interest in Allison Blake also causes significant friction with Sheriff Jack Carter.
metadata.title: Founder's Day
metadata.name: Eureka - Founder's Day

metadata.description: As the Founder's Day festivities continue, Carter and the others must accustom themselves to the new time line and how Dr. Grant fits into it. Unfortunately, re-acclimatization needs to occur on a steep learning curve.
metadata.title: A New World
metadata.name: Eureka - A New World

metadata.description: Dr. Isaac Parrish, the brilliant director of the Non-lethal Weapons Lab, is feeling a little undervalued these days. Then all his latent hostility goes viral, infecting everyone with such fury that no one is safe, especially Fargo.
metadata.title: All the Rage
metadata.name: Eureka - All the Rage

metadata.description: As Eureka celebrates Space Week, Dr. Ramsey unveils his cutting edge invention that could allow colonization of Mars. Unfortunately, a slight malfunction may cause it to incinerate Eureka before the dream is realized. Equally bad is that Eureka's go-to guy for crisis intervention has just gone to Boston to visit his daughter at Harvard.
metadata.title: The Story of O2
metadata.name: Eureka - The Story of O2

metadata.description: Claudia Donovan visits Eureka to see if Fargo's promises of wondrous devices are true, but she finds herself in the middle of a mystery suitable for Warehouse 13 when objects begin to appear randomly around the town and GD, and it must be solved before there are deadly consequences.
metadata.title: Crossing Over
metadata.name: Eureka - Crossing Over

metadata.description: Carter's camping trip with Kevin becomes a little scarier than ghost stories by the camp fire when a malfunction with the AI at Global Dynamics may turn some of them deadly. Elsewhere, Henry thinks about telling Grace the truth.
metadata.title: Momstrosity
metadata.name: Eureka - Momstrosity

metadata.description: Love is in the air as Carter gets fed up with Grant's pursuit of Allison, Zoe conceals her love and Henry courts Grace. But all the emotions may have to be put on simmer when people in town start turning to stone.
metadata.title: Stoned
metadata.name: Eureka - Stoned

metadata.description: The gang begins seeing visions of people from their pasts, while the town seems to be collapsing around them. Meanwhile, Dr. Grant gets involved with a mysterious faction.
metadata.title: The Ex-files
metadata.name: Eureka - The Ex-files

metadata.description: Dr. Grant attempts to return to 1947 but when Carter intrudes, they both wind up stuck in the past under the threat of altering present-day Eureka once again.
metadata.title: I'll Be Seeing You
metadata.name: Eureka - I'll Be Seeing You

metadata.description: Carter can't get into the Christmas spirit especially with the town surrounded by a force-field. Fargo organizes the GD holiday party, and Allison is full of holiday cheer.
metadata.title: O Little Town
metadata.name: Eureka - O Little Town

metadata.description: Zane pesters Jo for details she does not want to reveal. Carter problem-solves at Andy and S.A.R.A.H.'s wedding. Elsewhere, Zane's actions make him and Fargo unexpectedly airborne.
metadata.title: Lift Off
metadata.name: Eureka - Lift Off

metadata.description: Carter's duties expand to babysitting when Allison attends a medical conference, and Fargo finds his groove when a certain song is played. Meanwhile, a rocket scientist appears at Café Diem.
metadata.title: Reprise
metadata.name: Eureka - Reprise

metadata.description: Jo receives a technical boost to her crime-fighting ability with lenses that predict security breaches. Allison's headaches won't go away so Carter plans a vacation. Fargo, meanwhile, deals with an onslaught of volunteers when he announces a space mission with room for civilians.
metadata.title: Glimpse
metadata.name: Eureka - Glimpse

metadata.description: Jack deals with a bank robbery which may relate to the sudden gravity issues besetting the citizens of Eureka. Meanwhile, Fargo's rivalry with Isaac Parrish is boosted when he learns Holly and Parrish went on a date.
metadata.title: Up in the Air
metadata.name: Eureka - Up in the Air

metadata.description:
When Zoe comes home for a visit, Jo faces an angry woman who doesn't accept her fumbling explanations about Zane. This all fades to background noise, however, when they find everyone in Eureka unconscious and must find a way to work together so they can revive the town and beat Beverly before she gets hold of valuable data.


SYFY has this & "Of Mites and Men" Listed as episode 16 and does not have #17 "Clash of the Titans Listed"
metadata.title: Omega Girls
metadata.name: Eureka - Omega Girls

metadata.description:
Global Dynamics deals with two threats—a visit from Senator Wen and robotic bugs that can consume everything—it's unclear which is the bigger one. Meanwhile, Allison refuses to acknowledge any deficit with which the implants may have left her. 

SYFY has this & "Omega Girls" Listed as episode 16 and does not have #17 "Clash of the Titans Listed"
metadata.title: Of Mites and Men
metadata.name: Eureka - Of Mites and Men

metadata.description: The Eureka atmosphere becomes toxic when Department of Defense auditor comes to assess the team's relationships.
metadata.title: Clash of the Titans
metadata.name: Eureka - Clash of the Titans

files.name: Eureka - This One Time at Space Camp...

metadata.description: The Astraeus candidates go through their final interviews while Carter and Allison appeal their relationship audit.
metadata.title: This One Time at Space Camp...
metadata.name: Eureka - This One Time at Space Camp...

metadata.description: When an explosion in the Astraeus lab accidentally sends Andy to Titan the team must devise a plan to save him before it's too late! Eureka
metadata.title: One Small Step...
metadata.name: Eureka - One Small Step...

metadata.description: In the season finale - It's chaos in Eureka when an energy beam rips through main street but the Astraeus launch must go on...with or without Eureka intact.
metadata.title: One Giant Leap...
metadata.name: Eureka - One Giant Leap...

metadata.description: The Astraeus crew returns to Eureka four years later and must adapt to a myriad of changes, including a more oppressive version of Deputy Andy.
metadata.title: Lost
metadata.name: Eureka - Lost

metadata.description: Carter and Andy are jailed for trying to steal a piece of equipment to complete a device that Kevin has assembled to search for the Astraeus crew. Meanwhile, Holly comes up with a dangerous theory.
metadata.title: The Real Thing
metadata.name: Eureka - The Real Thing

metadata.description: Carter and Jo continue their search for the missing Astraeus crew. A surprising source confirms the new theory of the disaster, and offers to help them rescue the crew. Meanwhile, back at the lab, lives are at risk as more of the crew comes closer to the truth of their situation.
metadata.title: Force Quit
metadata.name: Eureka - Force Quit

metadata.description: When a smart fire experiment gets out of control, Carter and team discover that the Astraeus victims may be the cause. Meanwhile, Fargo deals with Holly's death, Grace struggles to maintain her relationship with Henry, and Allison fights her feelings about Jo.
metadata.title: Friendly Fire
metadata.name: Eureka - Friendly Fire

metadata.description: It's disaster drill day at GD and everyone must participate in order to see how well they would do in a disaster. Unfortunately the computer conducting the drill makes the simulation a reality. Elsewhere, Fargo undergoes risky interfaces with the Matrix to confirm Zane's findings.
metadata.title: Worst Case Scenario
metadata.name: Eureka - Worst Case Scenario

metadata.description: Fargo is convinced that Holly is still inside of the Matrix computer, but the DOD is determined to wipe its hard drive clean -- losing Dr. Marten forever.
metadata.title: Ex Machina
metadata.name: Eureka - Ex Machina

metadata.description: Carter's romantic surprise for Allison turns deadly when they're trapped in a sinking marine lab with time and oxygen quickly running out.
metadata.title: In Too Deep
metadata.name: Eureka - In Too Deep

metadata.description: While under the influence of a smart drug, Carter becomes a genius like everyone else in town and starts to change the laws of physics. Unfortunately, his condition soon endangers all of Eureka, including Allison's brother who is in town just to meet his new brother-in-law.
metadata.title: Smarter Carter
metadata.name: Eureka - Smarter Carter

metadata.description: Jack and Allison's perfect honeymoon is interrupted when sabotage is discovered in Eureka. Elsewhere, Holly faces another hurdle to remain intact.
metadata.title: The Honeymooners
metadata.name: Eureka - The Honeymooners

metadata.description: The Department of Justice arrives to investigate Grace, while Henry struggles with his conscience and Eureka is cut off from the world by a malfunctioning experiment that threatens to eradicate the town's populace.
metadata.title: Mirror, Mirror
metadata.name: Eureka - Mirror, Mirror

metadata.description: The people of Eureka are being kidnapped and replaced by body-doubles one by one unless Allison, Fargo and Zane can figure out how to avoid capture and save their town.
metadata.title: Double Take
metadata.name: Eureka - Double Take

metadata.description: In the series finale, wormholes randomly materialize around Eureka as the Department of Defense is set to shut the town.
metadata.title: Just Another Day
metadata.name: Eureka - Just Another Day
